descp2: A 1-D Tensor of length 4. Must be: `[1, rate_rows, rate_cols, 1]`. This is the input stride, specifying how far two consecutive patch samples are in the input. Equivalent to extracting patches with `patch_sizes_eff = patch_sizes + (patch_sizes - 1) * (rates - 1)`, followed by subsampling them spatially by a factor of `rates`. This is equivalent to `rate` in dilated (a.k.a. Atrous) convolutions.
